Function graph:
main()─┬─wakeup_leds()───irq_led_info()
       ├─network_connect()───enter_manually()
       ├─led_configure()
       ├─input_configure()
       ├─mqtt_configure()
       └─main_loop()─┬─irq_led_update()
                     └─irq_read_inputs()

LED State flows (2 seconds each, irq reads from array and updates 60 times per second)
        0 - wakeup(slow green fade in)
        1 - wifi-connected(flash green)
        2 - no-wifi-found(flash red)
        3 - mqtt-connected(flash gold)


irq_led_info()
        looks at two global variables:
                info_msg
                info_index
        updates every 1/60th of a second
        will incriment index, but never > 119
        to send a new message, just set:
                info_msg = new value
                THEN
                info_index = 0
        the last entry (info[*][119]) should always be:
                ((0,0,0),(0,0,0))
        will set the LEDs to the value specified by:
        info[msg][index] = ((r1,g1,b1),(r2,g2,b2))
